I am assuming the whole point is to avoid String#toLowerCase() and Character#toLowerCase() methods.
```
public String toLowerCase(String str) {
 char[] a = str.toCharArray();
 for (int i = 0; i < a.length; i++)
 if ('A' <= a[i] && a[i] <= 'Z')
 a[i] = (char) (a[i] - 'A' + 'a');
 return new String(a);
 }
```

